  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chips </strong>to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2156.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2156.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2156.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2156.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2156.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>chopped chives </strong>with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a small bowl</p>\n<p>Add a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and give everything a good mix up until all of the breadcrumbs are coated in the oil – this is your <strong>chive crumb</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2156.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
